50|$|Casten {{has served}} as {{president}} of the International District Energy Association and co-founder and chairman of the World Alliance for Decentralized Energy, which are trade associations that promote combined heat and power, district heating, and other forms of distributed generation. Casten also serves on numerous boards for energy-related institutions, has testified before the <b>energy</b> <b>committees</b> of the U.S. Congress, and served on the informal policy advisory team of then-presidential candidate Barack Obama in 2008.|$|R
